summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about countries' population, life expectancy, and fertility rates over time.

goals.question: What is the trend of population over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of year vs. pop
goals.rationale: This visualization will show how the population of countries has changed over time and if there are any patterns or trends.

goals.question: How does life expectancy vary across different countries?
goals.visualization: box plot of country vs. life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the distribution of life expectancy across different countries and if there are any outliers or differences between countries.

goals.question: What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of fertility vs. life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is any correlation between fertility rate and life expectancy and if there are any countries that deviate from the trend.

goals.question: How does population vary across different clusters?
goals.visualization: bar chart of cluster vs. pop
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the distribution of population across different cluster groups and if there are any differences in population size between clusters.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rate?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the distribution of fertility rate across all countries and if there are any patterns or trends in the data.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))

    plt.title('How does life expectancy vary across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
